         = \n| logo_alt          = \n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies''' is a Canadian [[Orthodox Judaism|Orthodox Jewish]] [[yeshiva]]. It is accredited by the Ontario [[Ministry of Education (Ontario)|Ministry of Education]] as a [[private university]] and has authority to grant bachelor's, master's, and doctorate degrees in [[Talmudic law]] and [[Judaic studies]].\n\n==History==\nIn 1970 a group of ten families from the [[Beth Medrash Govoha|BMG Institute for Advanced Learning]] of [[Lakewood, New Jersey]] moved to Toronto and founded the Toronto Kollel. The founders include: Rav [[Shlomo Eliyahu Miller]], the Rosh Kollel of the Kollel Avreichim Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies in Toronto and head of its [[Beis Din]] (rabbinical court) and Rav Yaakov Hirschman.\n\nKnown previously as the Institute for Advanced Talmudic Study - Kollel Avreichim, it was incorporated by letters patent dated October 9, 1970 as an institution of higher learning in theology, religious education, scholarship and research. \n.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kollel.com/ourfounders|title=Founders of Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies|accessdate=25 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810200920/http://kollel.com/ourfounders|archive-date=10 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Mission==\n* to provide post-secondary training programs in religious education and in research in higher Jewish learning for rabbis, teachers and educators;\n* to develop the devotional and spiritual life of its students;\n* to encourage its students to develop a mastery of the content of the [[Bible]], [[Judaic theology]], [[talmudic law]] and legal codes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cicic.ca/docs/postsec/Inst_for_Advanced_Judaic_Studies.pdf|title=Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies Act|accessdate=25 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Facility==\nThe building houses the 3,000-square-foot [[Bais Medrash]], classrooms, three book libraries, CD library, two computer online libraries, the [[Bar Ilan]] computer resource library, the Kol Halashon online Lecture library, meeting rooms, a kitchen and a dining room.\n\nThe Ladies Auxiliary maintains the Weinstock Memorial Library which is open to the public and runs a series of community lectures.\n\n==Kollel Toronto==\nKollel Toronto is an institution of learning consisting of a core group of scholars who are engaged in full-time Torah study at an advanced level\u2014headed by Roshei Kollel, Rav [[Shlomo Miller]] \u05e9\u05dc\u05d9\u05d8\"\u05d0 and Rav Yaakov Hirschman \u05e9\u05dc\u05d9\u05d8\"\u05d0.\n\n==Programs==\n* diplomas and certificates \n* Bachelor of Judaics\n* [[Bachelor of Talmudic Law]] (BTL)\n* [[Master of Rabbinic Studies|Master of Judaics]]\n* [[Master of Rabbinic Studies|Master of Talmudic Law]]\n* Doctor of Philosophy in Judaics\n* Doctor of Philosophy in Talmudic Law\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|https://kollel.com/iajs/}}\n\n{{Portal|Canada}}\n{{Ont post-secondary|d}}\n{{OrthodoxJudaism}}\n{{Conservative Judaism}}\n\n{{coord missing|Ontario}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Education in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Orthodox yeshivas in Canada]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Private universities and colleges in Canada]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1997]]\n\n\n{{Ontario-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{advert|date=June 2018}}\n{{third-party|date=June 2018}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n| name              = Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies \n| image             = \n| image_size        = \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = \n| latin_name        = \n| other_name        = <!--or, other_names-->\n| former_name       = <!--or, former_names-->\n| motto             = \n| motto_lang        = \n| mottoeng          = \n| top_free_label    = \n| top_free          = \n| type              = [[Private school|Private]] [[yeshiva]]\n| established       = {{start date|1997}}\n| closed            = <!-- {{end date|YYYY}} -->\n| founder           = \n| parent            = Kollel Toronto\n| religious_affiliation = [[Orthodox Judaism]]\n| academic_affiliation  = \n| endowment         = \n| budget            = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman          = \n| chairperson       = \n| chancellor        = \n| president         = \n| vice-president    = Albert Engel\n| superintendent    = \n| provost           = \n| vice_chancellor   = \n| rector            = \n| principal         = \n| dean              = Rabbi Nosson Hofman\n| director          = \n| head_label        = \n| head              = \n| academic_staff    = \n| administrative_staff = \n| students          = \n| undergrad         = \n| postgrad          = \n| doctoral          = \n| other             = \n| address           = 515 Coldstream Avenue\n| city              = [[Toronto]]\n| province          = [[Ontario]]\n| country           = [[Canada]]\n| postcode          = <!--or, postalcode or zipcode-->\n| coordinates       = <!-- {{Coord}} -->\n| campus            = \n| language          = \n| free2             = \n| colours           = [[Blue (color)|Blue]] and [[White (color)|White]] {{Color box|#0000FF}}{{color box|#FFFFFF}}\n| website           = {{URL|https://kollel.com/iajs/}}\n| logo              = \n| logo_size         = \n| logo_alt          = \n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies''' is a Canadian [[Orthodox Judaism|Orthodox Jewish]] [[yeshiva]]. It is accredited by the Ontario [[Ministry of Education (Ontario)|Ministry of Education]] as a [[private university]] and has authority to grant bachelor's, master's, and doctorate degrees in [[Talmudic law]] and [[Judaic studies]].\n\n==History==\nIn 1970 a group of ten families from the [[Beth Medrash Govoha|BMG Institute for Advanced Learning]] of [[Lakewood, New Jersey]] moved to Toronto and founded the Toronto Kollel. The founders include: Rav [[Shlomo Eliyahu Miller]], the Rosh Kollel of the Kollel Avreichim Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies in Toronto and head of its [[Beis Din]] (rabbinical court) and Rav Yaakov Hirschman.\n\nKnown previously as the Institute for Advanced Talmudic Study - Kollel Avreichim, it was incorporated by letters patent dated October 9, 1970 as an institution of higher learning in theology, religious education, scholarship and research. \n.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kollel.com/ourfounders|title=Founders of Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies|accessdate=25 July 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810200920/http://kollel.com/ourfounders|archive-date=10 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Mission==\n* to provide post-secondary training programs in religious education and in research in higher Jewish learning for rabbis, teachers and educators;\n* to develop the devotional and spiritual life of its students;\n* to encourage its students to develop a mastery of the content of the [[Bible]], [[Judaic theology]], [[talmudic law]] and legal codes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cicic.ca/docs/postsec/Inst_for_Advanced_Judaic_Studies.pdf|title=Institute for Advanced Judaic Studies Act|accessdate=25 July 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Facility==\nThe building houses the 3,000-square-foot [[Bais Medrash]], classrooms, three book libraries, CD library, two computer online libraries, the [[Bar Ilan]] computer resource library, the Kol Halashon online Lecture library, meeting rooms, a kitchen and a dining room.\n\nThe Ladies Auxiliary maintains the Weinstock Memorial Library which is open to the public and runs a series of community lectures.\n\n==Kollel Toronto==\nKollel Toronto is an institution of learning consisting of a core group of scholars who are engaged in full-time Torah study at an advanced level\u2014headed by Roshei Kollel, Rav [[Shlomo Miller]] \u05e9\u05dc\u05d9\u05d8\"\u05d0 and Rav Yaakov Hirschman \u05e9\u05dc\u05d9\u05d8\"\u05d0.\n\n==Programs==\n* diplomas and certificates \n* Bachelor of Judaics\n* [[Bachelor of Talmudic Law]] (BTL)\n* [[Master of Rabbinic Studies|Master of Judaics]]\n* [[Master of Rabbinic Studies|Master of Talmudic Law]]\n* Doctor of Philosophy in Judaics\n* Doctor of Philosophy in Talmudic Law\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n*{{official|https://kollel.com/iajs/}}\n\n{{Portal|Canada}}\n{{Ont post-secondary|d}}\n{{OrthodoxJudaism}}\n{{Conservative Judaism}}\n\n{{coord missing|Ontario}}\n\n[[Category:Education in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Orthodox yeshivas in Canada]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Private universities and colleges in Canada]]\n[[Category:1997 establishments in Ontario]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1997]]\n\n\n{{Ontario-school-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Institute_for_Advanced_Judaic_Studies"}
